  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As @samouss said it's not possible to use HTML tags in `<option>` but what I see in your title is that you want to get rid of counts. And for this, InstantSearch.js provides a solution, you can use a template for `item` that does not contain the count:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nwindow.search.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.menuSelect({\r\n    container,\r\n    attributeName: 'categories', // replace with the relevant attribute in your index \r\n    templates: {\r\n      item: '{{label}}',      \r\n    },   \r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nLet us know @emeagenciadigital ",
